    "During the initial periods, a large fraction of tasks are automated, leading to wage collapse similar to the aggressive AGI scenario as the economy enters region 2labor is abundant because of the rapid automation and comparatively low capital stock.",
    "However, over time, the economy accumulates more capital, making labor scarcer again.",
    "Around year 9, the economy has accumulated sucient capital so that it returns to region 1.",
    "Wages rise above A and start growing again in line with further (slower) advances in automation and further capital accumulation.",
    "This scenario illustrates the possibility that labor demand may collapse due to rapid automation but recover later because of a long tail of tasks that cannot be automated."
